reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Why did I choose these', 'author': 'PhotoGraphics', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I thought the easiest thing in the world would be to buy a handful of old fashioned wire clothes hangers for a small section of my walk-in closet - the kind my grandma has had hanging in her closet for 50 years, the ones she got free from the cleaners. No such luck, I spent an hour until I finally found these. What was once regarded as the cheapest hanger you could buy sells now for as much as five bucks each. No I am not making that up. And most of them want you to take 50 or even a hundred. I only needed a few to fill a small space and I purposely wanted wire because I’m hanging everyday tee shirts, not heavy winter jackets.HELPFUL HINTSFollowing are some hints based on what I learned (or already knew). First, I didn’t need or want wooden hangers. They are great for hanging coats but the design makes them take up too much space. And plastic? reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars I threw out my plastic hangers SO quick', 'author': 'Ti', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I needed new hangers so I decided to go ahead and try the Amazon brand since they're known for their quality, and man, these are great.You'd be surprised with how much space you'll save using these versus the standard, bulky plastic ones. reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Liked the first order so much, I ordered again!', 'author': 'T. Jackson', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'From the photo I\'ve included, you can see how crowded my closet is...you should have seen it before! This will probably be thinned out as soon as the weather gets warmer so I can put away the bulky sweaters. However, I can\'t get over how much I like these hangers! I\'ve wanted to try velvet hangers for awhile, but they were either too cheap, or way too expensive! The first box I ordered were the teal. They came in a big cardboard box with five plastic bags containing 10 hangers each. The colors were more vibrant than I expected from the photos. However, I was most impressed by their performance. I have a number of stretchy knit dresses, silky blouses, and sweaters, all that constantly slipped off the hangers to the floor, or if they stayed on, they tended to be stretched out. When I put these items on the velvet hangers; they stayed put. They are also less bulky than those terrible plastic hangers (and I don\'t even know if wire hangers are a thing outside laundromats). Now I can hang up more of the clothes that were either crammed into the drawer, or folded on top of the closet shelf, or even left in the laundry basket. I immediately decided I needed more of these things, but opted for a fun purple instead. They were of the same quality as before. So, I have a total of 100 hangers, and I have them ALL in use!Yes, they are lightweight and they seem somewhat "bendy". I don\'t think they would be suitable for a heavy winter coat. The heaviest item on the hangers are a few sweatshirts and lightweight hoodies. Most of my clothing is lightweight, stretchy, or slippery---usually all three. It\'s a relief to be able to open the closet and not find half my clothes on the floor, or having to re-hang things just because I had to move the hangers to look for something. I\'m careful about removing the hangers from the clothes or from the rack. In the past, I\'ve been careless and impatient with other hangers and managed to snap them in half. However, I\'ve taken reasonable care with these, and so far, none of them have broken or even gotten bent.I read a lot of reviews where customers have complained about fuzz and even color transferring onto their clothing, but that has not been my experience. I haven\'t noticed any transfer with the teal or purple hangers. Maybe certain other colors are problematic---I don\'t know. I also do not use these hangers for wet clothing that I take out of the washer to air dry. I still put wet or damp clothes on plastic hangers, or drape them over a rack. I was concerned that the water or moisture might damage the hangers. Again, I have had no problems of fuzz or transferred dye on my clothes. I\'ve had buyers\' regret from time to time with online purchases, but I am SO glad I took a chance and ordered these. I\'ve only had the hangers for about four months now, and if most of them last at least a year, I\'ll be happy. A lot of the really heavy plastic hangars seem to plasticize after some time and them just break. I bought these wood ones to help my wife with her closet organization. They look Sewell made, and I would expect them to perform well. The spring clips are strong and likewise seem well made.When I compare this hanger to my older hangars, the first thing that I notice is the size of the hook is smaller as is the gauge of the wire used to make the hook. However, upon close inspection the wood is finger jointed in the new hanger. But I picked one up at the store and could tell immediately that it was poor quality. The hangers were so rough that I got a splinter, and the pants hanging bar on the bottom was loose. I briefly considered how long it would take me to sand and finish each of the hangers so they wouldn't snag my clothing or my hands, or if I could con my husband into doing it. (NOTE: These poor quality hangers were NOT the ZOBERs I bought from Amazon.)Instead, I went home and ordered these ZOBER hangers from Amazon. I ordered them about 8 pm and they were delivered before I awakened this a.m. (Amazon delivery people are the best!) I was a little uneasy about ordering them because they looked so much like the poor quality ones I had seen in the store. And out of 8430 reviews on Amazon, two reviewers rated them poor, citing the rough finish and shoddy construction. I was so happy when I opened them and found them to be very good quality, smooth finish, attractive wood, and solid construction. One thing I would mention, they are listed as suit hangers, I suppose because there is also a provision for hanging a pair of pants. For a really good suit, I would go with a hanger whose shoulders actually curve forward to help retain the shape of the suit jacket shoulders. The contour of these hangers is more in a single plane, rather than curving forward. I think these are more appropriate for hanging casual jackets, sweaters, pants, shirts that one would want to keep from wrinkling, or fragile fabric that would be damaged by a wire hanger or cheap thin plastic hanger. I skipped the bushing altogether when putting the second hanger together.I do like that there are alternating heights of hooks, but I wish some had more space between them. There also should have been differing widths of the actual belt hooks.I am currently using these to hang my resistance ropes in my gym area, and I am latching the carabiners to the belt hooks, rather that hooking over like the pictures show for belts, or draping the ropes over. This allows me to see the label for each resistance rope. I would not have much confidence using this for actual belts because of the pilot hole size to screw hook issue. I would not be surprised to see the screws eventually strip out.I received these through Vine. Had these been a regular purchase, I would have returned. I could glue the screw hooks in place to insure the hangers are secure, but I should not have to. When I purchase a product, I expect it to work as advertised without me having to modify it to make it functional. Modifying to fit my personal use/needs is one thing, but doctoring something just to make it work like it should is another. I have 2 closets across from each other and hung a rod between them so I can pull this out of my closet and spread it out on the rod to choose which pants shorts or skirt I want to wear and put it back in my over pack closet more easily than if I were to go through separate hangers looking for something to wear. Doing it that way clothes tend to get pulled off the clips. These are very sturdy and I don't mind if my clothes have a mark from the clip. Better than falling off the clips onto the floor and getting wrinkles. I really love it. I previously bought another brand...it didn't hold up. This hanger seems it will last my lifetime. So it's nice looking, convenient, and just wish this company made a hanger for bras and tank tops. I may have to get more of these and just clip them instead of getting another brand where it would allow me to hang them on hooks. I love that I can spread out my clothes using the hangers hooks at both ends of the hanger. I've already bought a 2nd one. They're kinda expensive but worth it and I can see me buying more in my future. Oh and for those who don't have over stuffed closets, they will like that the hook has a swivel so it can remain in your closet while you choose the item you want to wear. I struggle with the top part.
